Security Architecture Decisions:
Defence in Depth:

3 tier security groups prevent lateral movement
Database never accessible from internet
App servers only reachable through load balancer
All data encrypted at rest with KMS
All data encrypted in transit with SSL

Least Privilege:

Each service has dedicated IAM role
Security groups allow minimum required traffic
Database only accepts app server connections
S3 bucket policy enforces HTTPS only

Monitoring and Response:

GuardDuty provides 24/7 threat detection
CloudTrail logs every API call permanently
VPC Flow Logs capture all network traffic
CloudWatch alarms trigger immediate SNS alerts
Security Hub provides unified security dashboard


Challenges Faced and Resolved:
Challenge 1:
RDS deletion protection prevented database deletion
Fixed by modifying RDS instance to disable protection first
Then deleted with final snapshot for data preservation
Challenge 2:
Two RDS databases running simultaneously
Identified dipesh-security-db still running from earlier practice
Deleted both databases correctly to avoid charges
Challenge 3:
AWS Config showed noncompliant resources
Investigated each finding and documented business justification
account-part-of-organizations noncompliant — expected for personal account
Shows real security analyst investigation skills
Challenge 4:
CloudFront account verification required
Documented configuration knowledge
Shows understanding of AWS account maturity requirements

